As a background: In RAP 3.21 we added the ability to handle and to intercept HTTP redirects with commit d4d5c380e7f94b8192a576780c1e4890c98fb322.

After some consideration, we believe that the suppression of the shutdown request belongs to the entry point, i.e. it should be possible to configure it differently for each entry point, as opposed to configuring it at the application level.

An example configuration in the `ApplicationConfiguration` could look as follows and include a new [`WebClient`](https://github.com/eclipse-rap/org.eclipse.rap/blob/9e37dde7eec6febb9c925bf6afbf321ccfa63942/bundles/org.eclipse.rap.rwt/src/org/eclipse/rap/rwt/client/WebClient.java) constant `DISABLE_SHUTDOWN_REQUEST`. This is just an additional property that is used during the initialisation of the entry point:

```java
Map<String, String> properties = new HashMap<String, String>();
properties.put( WebClient.DISABLE_SHUTDOWN_REQUEST, "true" );
application.addEntryPoint( "/", Demo.class, properties );
```

