When using CSP with script-src 'strict-dynamic' , this causes an error: _Content-Security-Policy: The page’s settings blocked an event handler (script-src-attr) from being executed because it violates the following directive: “script-src 'strict-dynamic' 'nonce-62d10451757d440c94d6f1e7f45aefcf'”_

Instead of setting the ondrop attribute, addEventHandler should be used here:
```
//currently: doc.getElement().setAttribute( "ondrop", "event.preventDefault();" );
doc.getElement().addEventListener( "ondrop", function ( event ) {
  event.preventDefault();
});
```
I am not sure if this fix is still necessary at all. The website that has been mentioned as example in the bugzilla does not exist anymore, so I tested it locally and removed this drop listener beforehand. D&D is possible in Firefox, Edge, Chrome and Opera, when the source is a Label. When the source is a Text, D&D is possible in all these browsers, except for Firefox, where the 'not allowed' icon is shown. So it seems to already be prevented somewhere else. Also, when I left the drop listener in, it never got an event when I initiated a drop.

